M a l e: Protarsomeres and mesotarsomeres 1 to 3 distinctly widened. Aedeagus (
Figs 157-159
) 0.93-0.96 mm long, strongly sclerotized, symmetrical. Basal bulb much longer than apical process of median lobe, latter with dorsal branch partly exposed, ventral branch oblique, slightly sinuate and gradually narrowed toward tip (lateral view). Parameres dorsally overlapping. Internal sac with large, robust and strongly sclerotized hook, joint to tuft of long spines.
